package org.drools.generated;

declare ShippingOrder
    orderId : String
    total : double
    shippingCost : double
end

rule "Free Shipping for Orders Over 100"
salience 100
when
    $order : ShippingOrder(total > 100, shippingCost == -1.0)
then
    modify($order) { setShippingCost(0.0) }
end

rule "Shipping Cost 5.0 for Orders Between 50 and 100"
salience 90
when
    $order : ShippingOrder(total >= 50, total <= 100, shippingCost == -1.0)
then
    modify($order) { setShippingCost(5.0) }
end

rule "Shipping Cost 10.0 for Orders Less Than 50"
salience 10
when
    $order : ShippingOrder(total < 50, shippingCost == -1.0)
then
    modify($order) { setShippingCost(10.0) }
end

This DRL code defines three rules to determine the `shippingCost` based on the `total` of a `ShippingOrder`. The rules are mutually exclusive and use salience to ensure only one rule fires per order, with higher priority given to larger orders. Each rule checks for an initial `shippingCost` value of `-1.0`, indicating that no shipping cost has been set yet.